{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784050422156", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-b70feb4becfa98cf", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "python3 -c \"\nimport re, html\nwith open('/tmp/fdaudio.html','r',encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    raw = f.read()\n# Remove scripts and styles\nraw = re.sub(r'<script[^>]*>.*?</script>', '', raw, flags=re.DOTALL)\nraw = re.sub(r'<style[^>]*>.*?</style>', '', raw, flags=re.DOTALL)\n# Replace block elements with newlines\nraw = re.sub(r'</(p|div|h[1-6]|li|tr|td|th|section|article|blockquote|pre)>', '\\n', raw, flags=re.IGNORECASE)\nraw = re.sub(r'<br\\s*/?>', '\\n', raw, flags=re.IGNORECASE)\n# Remove all remaining tags\nraw = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', '', raw)\nraw = html.unescape(raw)\n# Collapse whitespace\nraw = re.sub(r'\\n\\s*\\n', '\\n\\n', raw)\nraw = re.sub(r'[ \\t]+', ' ', raw)\nprint(raw[:2000])\n\" 2>&1 | head -80", "description": "Extract text from HTML paper"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "6fa048a7-4bf3-481f-994f-575f3d4d1d44", "uuid": "44f4e173-ed0c-4287-9a7d-ce8c584646a1"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b70feb4becfa98cf", "type": "tool_result", "content": "FdAudio: MeanFlow-Anchored Fréchet-Distance Post-Training for One-Step Text-to-Audio Generation\n\n Report GitHub Issue\n\n ×\n\n Title:\n\n Content selection saved. Describe the issue below:\n\n Description:\n\n Submit without GitHub\n Submit in GitHub\n\n arXiv is now an independent nonprofit!\n Learn more\n ×\n\n Back to arXiv\n\n Why HTML?\n\n Report Issue\n\n Back to Abstract\n\n Download PDF\n\nAbstract\n\nI Introduction\n\nII Related Work\n\nII-A Few-step T2A generation\n\nII-B MeanFlow one-step generation\n\nIII Method\n\nIII-A Fréchet-distance post-training\n\nIII-B MeanFlow anchor for multi-step preservation\n\nIV Experimental Setup\n\nIV-A Data\n\nIV-B Metrics\n\nIV-C Training\n\nV Results\n\nV-A System-level comparisons\n\nV-B MeanFlow anchor\n\nV-C Encoders for multi-representation FD-loss\n\nVI Conclusion\n\nReferences\n\n License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0\n\narXiv:2607.10421v1 [eess.AS] 11 Jul 2026\n\nFdAudio: MeanFlow-Anchored Fréchet-Distance Post-Training for One-Step Text-to-Audio Generation\n\nKuan-Po Huang⋆, Bo-Ru Lu†, Ho-Lam Chung⋆, Shih-Hsin Wang⋆, Hung-yi Lee⋆\n†This work is unrelated to the author’s position at Amazon.\n\nAbstract\n\nWhile recent few-step sampling text-to-audio generation models like MeanAudio substantially accelerate generation by modeling average velocities, their strict one-step generation quality still lags significantly behind multi-step counterparts.\nWe propose FdAudio to bridge this gap. Unlike MeanAudio, which relies solely on regression against target velocity fields, our post-training approach optimizes the final one-step distribution directly across pre-trained embedding spaces via a multi-representation Fréchet-distance (FD) loss. Crucially, to prevent the multi-step degradation that naive post-training with FD-loss causes, we introduce a MeanFlow consistency objective as a structural anchor.", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "6fa048a7-4bf3-481f-994f-575f3d4d1d44", "uuid": "be15c6a6-7ea1-4fdc-8645-17d9fcc38e1a", "timestamp": "2026-07-14T17:34:08.575Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "FdAudio: MeanFlow-Anchored Fréchet-Distance Post-Training for One-Step Text-to-Audio Generation\n\n Report GitHub Issue\n\n ×\n\n Title:\n\n Content selection saved. Describe the issue below:\n\n Description:\n\n Submit without GitHub\n Submit in GitHub\n\n arXiv is now an independent nonprofit!\n Learn more\n ×\n\n Back to arXiv\n\n Why HTML?\n\n Report Issue\n\n Back to Abstract\n\n Download PDF\n\nAbstract\n\nI Introduction\n\nII Related Work\n\nII-A Few-step T2A generation\n\nII-B MeanFlow one-step generation\n\nIII Method\n\nIII-A Fréchet-distance post-training\n\nIII-B MeanFlow anchor for multi-step preservation\n\nIV Experimental Setup\n\nIV-A Data\n\nIV-B Metrics\n\nIV-C Training\n\nV Results\n\nV-A System-level comparisons\n\nV-B MeanFlow anchor\n\nV-C Encoders for multi-representation FD-loss\n\nVI Conclusion\n\nReferences\n\n License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0\n\narXiv:2607.10421v1 [eess.AS] 11 Jul 2026\n\nFdAudio: MeanFlow-Anchored Fréchet-Distance Post-Training for One-Step Text-to-Audio Generation\n\nKuan-Po Huang⋆, Bo-Ru Lu†, Ho-Lam Chung⋆, Shih-Hsin Wang⋆, Hung-yi Lee⋆\n†This work is unrelated to the author’s position at Amazon.\n\nAbstract\n\nWhile recent few-step sampling text-to-audio generation models like MeanAudio substantially accelerate generation by modeling average velocities, their strict one-step generation quality still lags significantly behind multi-step counterparts.\nWe propose FdAudio to bridge this gap. Unlike MeanAudio, which relies solely on regression against target velocity fields, our post-training approach optimizes the final one-step distribution directly across pre-trained embedding spaces via a multi-representation Fréchet-distance (FD) loss. Crucially, to prevent the multi-step degradation that naive post-training with FD-loss causes, we introduce a MeanFlow consistency objective as a structural anchor.", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
