{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-874547b151adbef3", "type": "tool_result", "content": "=== arxiv (5 results) ===\n  1. FlashAR: Efficient Post-Training Acceleration for Autoregressive Image Generation\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.09430\n     [authors=Junkang Zhou, Yefei He, Feng Chen, Weijie Wang, Bohan Zhuang | published=2026-05-10 | primary_category=cs.CV | id=2605.09430]\n  2. Fréchet Radiomic Distance (FRD): A Versatile Metric for Comparing Medical Imaging Datasets\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.01496\n     [authors=Nicholas Konz, Richard Osuala, Preeti Verma, Yuwen Chen, Hanxue Gu, Haoyu Dong, Yaqian Chen, Andrew Marshall, Lidia Garrucho, Kaisar Kushibar, Daniel M. Lang, Gene S. Kim, Lars J. Grimm, John M. Lewin, James S. Duncan, Julia A. Schnabel, Oliver Diaz, Karim Lekadir, Maciej A. Mazurowski | published=2024-12-02 | primary_category=cs.CV | id=2412.01496]\n  3. FdAudio: MeanFlow-Anchored Fréchet-Distance Post-Training for One-Step Text-to-Audio Generation\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.10421\n     [authors=Kuan-Po Huang, Bo-Ru Lu, Ho-Lam Chung, Shih-Hsin Wang, Hung-yi Lee | published=2026-07-11 | primary_category=eess.AS | id=2607.10421]\n  4. The Discrete and Semi-continuous Fréchet Distance with Shortcuts via Approximate Distance Counting and Selection Techniques\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/1310.5245\n     [authors=Rinat Ben Avraham, Omrit Filtser, Haim Kaplan, Matthew J. Katz, Micha Sharir | published=2013-10-19 | primary_category=cs.CG | id=1310.5245]\n  5. Representation Fréchet Loss for Visual Generation\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.28190\n     [authors=Jiawei Yang, Zhengyang Geng, Xuan Ju, Yonglong Tian, Yue Wang | published=2026-04-30 | primary_category=cs.CV | id=2604.28190]\n\n=== openreview (5 results) ===\n  1. \n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=4JhDEgHQ6a\n     [authors= | rank=1 | id=4JhDEgHQ6a]\n  2. \n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=4HUvroOypm\n     [authors= | rank